HEADWORD: Algarovilla
<hw>Al`ga*ro*vil"la</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The
agglutinated seeds and husks of the legumes of a South American tree
(<spn>Inga Marthae</spn>). It is valuable for tanning leather, and as a
dye.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

